name: 5 Blends Coffee House
description: Warm and friendly environment, 5 blends of coffee to choose from and knowledgeable baristas to explain.  Small gallery seating downstairs in basement. Also pastries, sandwiches and paninis to eat in and take out.

name: Cambridge Public Library - 3rd Floor
description: This floor has computer desks, community meeting rooms (at affordable rates) and a café.
address: 7 Lion Yard, Grand Arcade, Cambridge, CB2 3QD

name: Cambridge Public Library - 1st Floor (Fiction)
description: This is likely to be the busiest floor.
address: 7 Lion Yard, Grand Arcade, Cambridge, CB2 3QD

name: Urban Larder
description: Little cafe and deli shop on Mill Road.
address: 9 The Broadway Mill Road, Cambridge CB1 3AH

name: Cambridge Public Library - 2nd Floor (Non-Fiction and Reference)
description: Brilliant for group study, but don't forget being a public library you are likely to get groups of A-Level & GSCE students working together here in peak college/school term.
address: 7 Lion Yard, Grand Arcade, Cambridge, CB2 3QD

name: UL - North Front Corridor
description: Bookshelves work to form booths with large desks that seats two people. The desk faces the busy North Front walk way and is close to the Tea Room.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: Moore Library - 1st Floor
description: Large quantity of study spaces with good views of the main site. A lot of natural light and generally fairly quiet place to work.
restriction: Validated University card access outside staffed hours

name: Novi
description: Coffee shop come cocktail bar. Really encourage that people use their space as an office.

name: UL - Fourth Floor Landing
description: One of the most historical looking parts of the library, populated with portraits of former UL librarians.  Dark, heavy furniture means that although there is plenty of natural light, it still feels cosy.  The space is not always available as it is occasionally used as meeting space by Library staff.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: Black Cat Café
description: A New Zealand style cafe focusing on preparing food made from good quality produce. The first flat white in Cambridge!

name: Cafe de Paris
description: Small, relaxed corner café serving a range of continental style cakes, pastries and sandwiches. A couple of small outdoor tables on the pavement.

name: Caffe Nero (Fitzroy St)
description: Italian coffee chain near Grafton Centre. Plenty of seating upstairs too.

name: Seeley Library
description:
The Seeley Library entrance is on the ground floor of the History Faculty building on the Sidgwick Site. Most desks have plugs and WIFI is available. There are also Managed Cluster computers with a printer, and a photocopier.

See the JCR space for an area suitable for group work with a café, seating, tables and WIFI. Found on the first floor of the Faculty.
address:
Faculty of History
West Road
Cambridge
CB3 9EF
restriction: None

name: Starbucks: Regent Street
description: Modern, spacious coffee shop with a large table suitable for working together or with lots of kit. Laptop friendly with bar style tables and chairs around the sides of the space. Plug points available. Environment very suited to studying.

name: Costa Coffee (Sidney Street)
description: Counter-service coffee chain offering hot drinks, iced coolers, sweet snacks and sandwiches.

name: Caffe Nero (Market St)
description: Italian coffee chain.

name: Costa Coffee (Grand Arcade)
description: A small seating area on the ground floor of the Grand Arcade in quite an open area, so lots of people passing by.
address:
Unit K5, Grand Arcade,
St Andrews Street,
Cambridge, CB2 3AX.

name: Jamaica Blue (Lion Yard/Grand Arcade)
description: Table service café with friendly staff and lovely food and coffee.
address:
Grand Arcade,
St Andrews Street,
Cambridge,
CB2 3AX.

name: Starbucks (Christ's Lane)
description: Part of the Starbucks chain.
address:
Unit 4
6 Christs Lane
Cambridge
ENG
CB1 1NP

name: Cambridge Judge Business School Cafe
description: Situated on the first floor of Cambridge Judge Business School, this cafe offers hot and cold drinks, as well as sandwiches and snacks. An open and light space, it offers tables for working in groups, or alone, as well as some comfy sofa seating.
address: Cambridge Judge Business School, Trumpington Street, Cambridge, CB2 1AG

name: Cambridge Cookery School Cafe
description: Large, airy cafe serving excellent coffee, croissants and international cuisine.
address:
School House
Homerton Gardens
Purbeck Road
Cambridge
CB2 8EB

name: Charlie's Coffee Company
description: Independent, family-owned cafe, famed for its coffee and its pizza

name: Whale Cafe
description: Cafe in the Zoology Museum, above the museum reception. Getting busy during the school holidays.
address:
New Museum Site
Downing Street
Cambridge, CB2 3EJ

name: Starbucks (Grand Arcade)
description: On the first floor of the Grand Arcade near the lifts by John Lewis. Fairly busy but generally quieter than the ground floor of the shopping centre.
address:
Unit 35, Grand Arcade,
St Andrew's St,
Cambridge,
CB2 3AX.

name: Livingstones Coffee Shop
description: Built in the space between a church and the building next door, this cafe offers food, homemade cakes and drinks. Friendly customer service.
address: 43 St Andrew's Street, City Centre, Cambridge, CB2 3AR.

name: Zio Mario
description: A cafe offering artisan coffee, pasta and baked goods. A bright space with good seating and some background noise. Limited plug sockets.

name: Espresso Lane
description: A small cafe in the centre of Cambridge. This café is tucked away down a lane and has limited seating. They sell food and drinks, as well as plenty of Vegetarian options. Most likely will need to make a purchase to study here.

name: The Buttery, Sidgwick Site
description: Inexpensive food and drink (including pastries) on the Sigdwick site. Picnic benches outside are a great spot if sunny.

name: The Anchor
description: Centrally-located pub with views over the River Cam. Good spot for a pint while getting some work done.

name: The Copper Kettle (Agora)
description: Situated directly opposite King's College, The Copper Kettle is the perfect place to sit and watch the world go by. With huge windows looking out onto King's Parade, you can people-watch while getting some work done.

name: The Garden Kitchen
description: Cafe on Mill Road serving hot and cold breakfast and lunch.

name: Hot Numbers Coffee (Trumpington Street)
description: This independent medium-sized cafe is opposite Engineering and close to the business school and the Fitzwilliam Museum. It is very popular so is often busy, sells good food and excellent coffee.

name: Crepe Affaire
description: Fairly new to Cambridge, this Crepe house is pretty popular at the weekend. Suprisingly warm the day we visited (nothing to do with the weather outside) but not too bad for working in a small group

name: Grads Cafe
description: Open space with lots of natural light from the huge windows that make up two of the walls. Mixed seating from tables to comfy chairs makes this a good place to study.
address: The University Centre, Granta Place, Cambridge, CB2 1RU

name: Fitzbillies
description: Fitzbillies is a bit of a Cambridge institution and is well-known for their chelsea buns. A good, vibrant cafe to work in. Very popular first thing in the morning for people looking to get a coffee and do some work. Has excellent wifi.

name: Cambridge Judge Business School Information Centre - Mezzanine
description: Situated on the mezzanine floor of the Cambridge Judge Business School, this space has desks for solo work as well as PCs, and a number of beanbags.
address: Cambridge Judge Business School, Trumpington Street, Cambridge, CB2 1AG
restriction: Members of the University only. Others by prior arrangement. Mezzanine entrance swipe card access only.

name: The Maypole
description: Friendly, family-run, free house pub with plenty of outdoor seating and good, homemade food. A popular place to meet up with friends, but can get very busy.

name: Computer Laboratory Cafe
description: Bright and airy space in the computer lab, in non busy times you should be able to sit and work without having to keep buying coffee.
address: William Gates Building, JJ Thompson Avenue, Cambridge CB3 0FD

name: West Café (Hauser Forum)
description: The Cafe at the Hauser Forum in West Cambridge is privately run and serves Costa Coffee. It gets busy at lunchtime.
address: Hauser Forum, 3 Charles Babbage Rd, Cambridge, CB3 0GT

name: Caffe Nero (Kings Parade)
description: In a busy location, this is usually quite full of tourists in the summer. The further back you go the more comfortable the seating. They don't advertise that they sell Flat Whites but they do.
address: Cambridge Kings Parade, 17 Kings Parade Cambridge, CB2 1SP

name: Liutaio
description: Cafe and music shop with Eastern and Western food. Quiet in the day. Music shop selling bowed stringed instruments adds to the vibe.

name: Tatties
description: A Cambridge institution! A cafe with plenty of seating including outdoor tables.
address: 11 Sussex St, Hobson St, Cambridge CB1 1PA

name: Trockel, Ulmann & Freunde
description: Cosy German cafe, famous for its soups. Central, but a little off the beaten track.

name: The Senate
description: Mediterranean in style, the Senate is a busy cafe close to the centre of town. It's picturesque location means it's popular with visitors to Cambridge.

name: The Pint Shop
description: Pub of the keg, cask and gin variety. Pretty fancy and pricey but a nice environment to work in on a quiet afternoon.

name: Cafe Abantu
description: Hip and busy cafe in the centre of Cambridge with good coffee, good food and cosy seating.

name: English - IT Training Suite
description: A bookable group study room for about twelve people with laptops and projector by request.

name: Espresso Library
description: Trendy cycling cafe with a social and sporty vibe, though often populated by people working on laptops.

name: Moore Library - Ground Floor
description: The Ground floor is the main entrance, enquiry and staff area. As such, has limited study areas and is generally the noisest part of the library. Despite motion activated lighting can be quite a 'dark' area to work compared to the other floors.
restriction: validated University card access outside staffed hours

name: Mill Lane Seminar Room (Land Economy)
description: Bookable seminar room administered by Mill Lane Library
restriction: Must be booked at Mill Lane Issue Desk

name: Mill Lane Main Library (Land Economy)
description: Contains approximately 50 study spaces with large desks and wooden and comfortable chairs.

name: Moore Library - 2nd Floor
description: A smaller area than the first floor but if you don't mind the sound ot the wind whistling through the roof, this is quite pleasant place to work. Also, excellent views of the rest of the site including the grass roof of the central core building.
restriction: Validated University card access outside staffed hours

name: UL - South Front 5
description: Located within the book shelves, there are usually a few people looking for books, but this is otherwise a quiet space.  This floor looks out over the Cambridge skyline and onto the main walkway past the Library. This space is included in Spacefinder as an example of the many open-shelf areas in the UL where it is possible to work.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: Cambridge Brew House
description: Pub/microbrewery with trendy decor. Student friendly. Excellent food and even better beer. Lots of tables. Large bookable room upstairs.

name: Benets Cafe
description: A small cafe, with a bonus ice-cream bar, directly opposite King's College Chapel. Good to study in but you need to buy regular drinks to avoid being asked to leave.

name: Le Patissier
description: Cosy daytime cafe in a touristy location.

name: Costa (Hills Road)
description: Not just another Costa. This is the best Costa in Cambridge bar none. Great coffee and snacks.

name: Astronomy: Library Room B
description: In the historic Cambridge Observatory building (1823).  This room has books on physics, mathematics and computing.  Also a set of Undergraduate Reference Books.
address:
Institute of Astronomy
Madingley Road
Cambridge
CB3 0HA
restriction: Steps at front of building.  Narrow corridors.

name: Philosophy - Computer Area
description: A small area with PCs, printing and scanning facilities
address:
Raised Faculty Building
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DA

name: Philosophy - Reading Room
description: Quiet working area with a variety of seating and desk space.
address:
Raised Faculty Building
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DA

name: SPS Library - Ground Floor
description: The ground floor area offers a variety of study spaces including two individual study desks and beanbags within the book collection.

name: Education Library - Lily Pad 2
description: A popular study area, on the upper floor of the Library. Spacious desks, some by large windows looking over the trees to Hills Road, others with views across to Homerton College. Access to plugs for laptops, computers and WIFI. Best for solo study and research.
restriction: DMB has access restrictions where Library is located; card controlled; Faculty Reception staff on duty during office hours

name: The Devonshire Arms
description: Milton Brewery Real Ale Pub with front and back space that have wooden booths and large tables.

name: GU/CUSU Lounge
description: Located inside the Cambridge University Students' Union and Graduate Union building, the GU/CUSU Lounge is a comfy, friendly, sociable place to work. It has comfortable leather armchairs, bar stools alongside raised surfaces, as well as more traditional desks and chairs. All students at the University of Cambridge are welcome to use the lounge.
address:
Cambridge University Students' Union and Graduate Union Building
17 Mill Lane
Cambridge
CB2 1RX
restriction: Open to all Cambridge students

name: The Locker Cafe
description: Friendly artisan cafe, breakfasts, brunches & lunches, art displays, music evenings, poetry readings, private event hire. Vegan & Vegetarian Friendly. Serves their own blend coffee, T2 teas, homemade cakes and slices, paninis, toasties and soup which are all locally sourced.

name: The Snug (Lensfield Road)
description: Being a bar expect it to be busy at lunch and in the evenings. They also have cocktail making classes that can be earlier in the day so can be raucous occasionally. Early morning and mid afternoon will be quieter but with a buzz of work and people around you. Great beer and very reasonably priced food. The Chilli Cheese Fries are amazing.

name: Cambridge Judge Business School Information Centre - Ground Floor
description: Situated on the ground floor of the Cambridge Judge Business School, this space has desks for solo work, a large table for silent group work, and dedicated Bloomberg terminals.
address: Cambridge Judge Business School, Trumpington Street, Cambridge, CB2 1AG
restriction: Members of the University only. Others by prior arrangement. Electronic badge entry for School members only after 17:00.

name: Language Centre: The John Trim Centre (Old Music School)
description:
Language learning centre, open space plus private space.  
Learn Tagalog or write your thesis! All welcome!
address:
The Language Centre, University of Cambridge
5, Downing Place
Cambridge
CB2 3EL

name: Jesus Green
description: A large space which includes a skate park and playground, there are benches to sit on and wide open spaces to sit on the grass, as well as Jesus Green Lido (an outdoor swimming pool) on the edge of the park beside the River Cam. There are fewer benches than some parks, but the space is wide and you can escape the worst of the traffic sounds.

name: Divinity Library - Mezzanine
description: The mezzanine area of the library with study spaces.
restriction: Main entrance to faculty closes at 17:00. Closed at lunchtime from 12:55-14:00 during vacation.

name: Granta Pub
description: Relaxing riverside pub with free Wi-Fi and good food. Also has a nice deck space when the weather is good

name: MML - Beit Library
description: Specialist German collection with 6 seats at shared desks.
address:
Modern & Medieval Languages Library
University of Cambridge
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DA

name: MML - Second floor
description: Quiet study spaces close to MML Library collections. A combination of individual study desks and shared tables.
address:
Modern & Medieval Languages Library
University of Cambridge
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DA

name: Whipple Main Library, Levels 3 & 4
description: Bench-style seating, high ceilings, wonderful sense of space. Close to bookshelves for easy access to resources and browsing.
address:
Whipple Library
Department of History and Philosophy of Science
Free School Lane
Cambridge CB2 3RH
restriction: Access via main library entrance (use swipecard entrance after 17:30 in full term)

name: Economics - Main Library Space
description: There are over 130 desk spaces on two levels, with a mixture of chairs. Lots of natural daylight.
address:
Austin Robinson Building
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DB
restriction: Access after 16:30 (Mon-Fri), and all day on Saturdays by University ID card (needs to be activated by Faculty of Economics Custodian: Mon-Fri: 9:00-16:00)

name: Psychology - common room
description: Student common room, with hot drink and snack vending machines, next to the Library.
address:
Department of Psychology 
Downing Street 
Cambridge 
CB2 3EB
restriction: Access through a controlled reception area.

name: Le Gros Franck
description: Quiet French café offering coffee and pastries.

name: MML - First floor
description: Large and individual study desks in amongst the collection, for quiet study.
address:
Modern & Medieval Languages Library
University of Cambridge
Sidgwick Avenue
Cambridge
CB3 9DA

name: The Mill
description:
Real ale pub situated right by the river, voted CAMRA pub of the year in 2015. A great place to study while having a hearty lunch and a pint. The Mill plays vinyl on a radiogram in the main bar, has a collection of boards games and a 'snug area' which seats 16 people. Many regard it as the best pub in Cambridge.

@TheMillCam

name: Hot Numbers Coffee (Gwydir Street)
description: Set in a former brewery building, Hot Numbers is a trendy café specialising in coffee.  Large bench tables make it good for group discussion.  Daytimes are quieter, evenings there tend to be events held and it can get busy.
address: Dale's Brewery, Gwydir Street, Cambridge, CB1 2LJ

name: Creams Cafe
description: Dessert cafe in the Leisure Park, open late, until 11 pm.
address:
Unit F1, 
Cambridge Leisure Park, 
Cambridge CB1 7DY

name: ARC Cafe
description: Food and drink in the Alison Richard Building on the Sidgwick site. Lots of seating inside and some picnic style tables and benches outside. Hot food range is limited.

name: SPS Library - Computer Study Area
description: Another reading area on the upper floor with PCs and a number of large study desks, some of which look out over the ground floor.

name: Parker’s Piece
description: This wide open space is located between Mill Road and the centre of town, and is easily accessible by foot or bike. There are trees and benches around the edges of the common, and various eateries nearby (including café and chairs at one corner) for anybody looking for a break.

name: Picturehouse Cambridge Cafe/Bar
description: The café bar is bright and airy with plenty of seating, including some sofas.  It is a busy and animated space, with high turnover; expect to buy regular drinks to keep a table.

name: The Free Press
description: A small, cosy pub that is quiet during the day and lively in the evening.
address: The Free Press Pub, 7 Prospect Row, Cambridge, CB1 1DU

name: Coldhams Cafe
description: Based in the C3 Church Centre, Coldhams Lane.  Large bright welcoming cafe serving coffee, cakes, pastries and snacks.  Outside seating area on patio, free wi-fi.
address:
C3 Centre, 
Coldhams Lane,
Cambridge 
CB1 3HR

name: CB2
description: Informal café and bookshop serving food and drink. Easily accessible from the Grafton Centre.

name: Laundress Green
description: A popular patch of grass by the Mill Pond where students and tourists gather. Overlooking the river and all the punting action this is one of Cambridge's iconic 'beauty spots'. Find a space to study but beware the cow pats as cattle are free to graze here.

name: Medical Library Shhh Space
description:
A room for silent, individual study located in the University of Cambridge Medical Library.

The library serves staff and students of the University of Cambridge, and NHS staff in the East of England region. The library is located on the Addenbrooke's site.
address:
University of Cambridge School of Clinical Medicine
Cambridge Biomedical Campus
Cambridge
CB2 0SP
restriction: The space can be used by staff and students of the University, or NHS staff in the East of England region.

name: Music: Faculty Graduate Room
description: This room is part of the old building and provides a study area reserved for Music Faculty graduate students.
restriction: This room is for use by Music Faculty graduate students only during library opening hours

name: Haddon: Main Reading Room
description: This traditional reading room offers 8 large tables seating 4 people each and 2 window tables seating 2 each.
restriction: Library opening hours only (broadly = office hours)

name: Haddon: McBurney Room
description: A room mainly given over to book collections, but with a couple of tables: seating 4 in the North West corner and 2 in the South West corner.
restriction: Library opening hours only (broadly = office hours)

name: Cornerstone Cafe
description: A friendly cafe associated with the St Philips Church Centre. Coffee, cakes and hot and cold meals served. A good place to work with some background noise.

name: Red Bull
description: Comfy Newnham pub

name: Chill #02
description: Modern cafe with vintage style, set within the Ibis hotel. Artisan Brazilian, Kenyan and Ethiopian coffee as well as pizza, homemade baguettes and salads.

name: Fitzwilliam Museum Reading Room
description: The Reading Room is at the Courtyard Entrance of the Museum. A relaxed, air-conditioned space close to the Museum café, which offers two library tables, seating 8 people in total, with attractive views onto the Grove Lodge garden.
address:
Fitzwilliam Museum
Trumpington Street
Cambridge 
CB2 1RB
restriction: Have to be let in/out by member of staff. If consulting library material please make an appointment (materials must be fetched). Otherwise anyone welcome to make use of the space when available.

name: Christ’s Pieces
description: A Victorian park in the centre of town, Christ’s Pieces lies between the city centre and Grafton Centre. There are tennis courts at the north-west corner and in the south-east corner lies a bowling green.

name: Fitzwilliam Museum
description: The Fitzwilliam Museum is a large arts and antiquities museum.  A large museum free to access, with 3 floors of exhibitions and alcoves or benches in most galleries

name: Fitzwilliam Museum Café
description: The Courtyard Café is located within the Fitzwilliam Museum, next to the gift shop.  The Courtyard Café is reasonably large, with a set daily menu as well as hot drinks and snacks.

name: Maths Cafe
description: Based at the Centre for Mathematical Sciences near the Moore Library, this is a great base for solo and group study.

name: 2nd View Coffee Shop (Waterstones Cafe)
description: Spacious cafe with plenty of plug sockets and varying sizes of tables for all kinds of work.

name: UL - Manuscripts Reading Room
description: The Manuscripts Reading Room is open to those doing further, specialist research.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use.  Undergraduates must provide a letter from their DoS.

name: Geography Library - Reading Room
description: Main library reading room
address:
Department of Geography
Downing Place
Cambridge
CB3 2EN

name: Psychology - traditional study rooms
description: Small Library with two study rooms containing carrel desks and larger desks. The main room has comfy leather armchairs.
address:
Department of Psychology 
Downing Street 
Cambridge 
CB2 3EB
restriction: Access through a controlled reception area.

name: Medical Library Share Space
description:
A collaborative working area with a mixture of furniture located in the University of Cambridge Medical Library.

The library serves staff and students of the University of Cambridge, and NHS staff in the East of England region. The library is located on the Addenbrooke's site.
address:
University of Cambridge School of Clinical Medicine
Box 111 Cambridge Biomedical Campus
Cambridge
CB2 0SP
restriction: Access restricted to members of the University and NHS staff.

name: Balfour & Newton - Newton Room
description: The room has seating for 12 people and also houses the Library photocopier. It is separate from the main seating area so could be used for group work.
restriction: Users without card access to the Department must go to the Reception desk.

name: Balfour & Newton - Main Library
description: The main area of the Library has seating for 49 people plus five desks with PCs. The seating area is in the oldest part of the building under a high domed ceiling.
restriction: Users without card access to the Department must go to the Reception desk.

name: UL - South Wing Corridor
description: This desk is on the South Wing Corridor going towards the Reading Room, meaning that it is in close walking distance of resources.  Although it is a quiet space, there are others walking by.  The desk has a nice view as it looks out onto the Library courtyard.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: UL - South Reading Room
description: **Prototype Library Space** Temporarily refurbished as part of the Protolib project, this room has dark squishy leather chairs and soft fabric sofas with throws.  Vintage lamps and adjustable uplighters make the room a cosy place to read.  Light and airy, it looks out onto the courtyard garden.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: UL - Reading Room South Corridor
description: This desk is on the south corridor to the Reading Room, meaning that it is in close walking distance of resources.  Although it is a quiet space, there are others walking by.  The desk looks out on the Library courtyard.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: UL - North Wing Corridor
description: This desk is on the North Wing corridor towards the Reading Room, meaning that it is in close walking distance of resources.  Although it is a quiet space, there are other walking by.  The desk has a nice view as it looks out onto the Library courtyard.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: Criminology - First floor
description: 28 workspaces, a mixture of single desks and shared tables. As a specialist postgrad library some desks are reserved for individual users and are not available for general use, but undergrads very are welcome
address: Radzinowicz Library, Institute of Criminology, University of Cambridge, Sidgwick Avenue, Cambridge CB3 9DA
restriction: University card required for library entry.

name: SPS Library - Main Reading Area
description: The main reading area reached via of a flight of stairs with a range of desks with plug sockets, lots of natural daylight and WIFI.

name: Computer Laboratory Library - Computer Desks
description: These computers are provided for members of the Computer Laboratory, but when they are not in use the desks can be used by anyone for quiet study.
address:
Computer Laboratory,
William Gates Building,
15 JJ Thomson Avenue,
Cambridge.
CB3 0FD

name: UL - North Reading Room
description: **Prototype Library Space** Temporarily refurbished as part of the Protolib Project.  This modern and spacious room has large tables with room to spread out, floor and desk lamps, and access to power points.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: UL - Tea Room
description: Teas, coffee, breakfast and lunch are available in this popular Tea Room.  Ideal for group work or a break from serious study.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: The Coffee House Cambridge
description: A café in the suburb of Addenbrookes. 15 minute walk or 5 minute cycle from Addenbrookes hospital. The Coffee House provides a lot of choices for hot and cold food, as well as deserts.

name: Medical Library Read Space
description: The reading room in the Medical Library. Large individual desks, couches and study pods.
address:
University of Cambridge School of Clinical Medicine
Cambridge Biomedical Campus
Cambridge
CB2 0SP
restriction: Access is restricted to members of the University, and NHS staff working in the East of England region.

name: UL - South Front Corridor
description: Bookshelves work to form booths with large desks that seats two people. The desk faces the busy South Front walk way.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: UL - AOI East Asian Reading Room
description: The Aoi is modern looking, providing a quiet space with large desks and comfy chairs.
address: Cambridge University Library, West Road, Cambridge, CB3 9DR
restriction: For information on how to access the UL, please see: http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/plan-your-visit/admissions/who-can-use

name: Starbucks (Fitzroy Street)
description: Part of the Starbucks chain.
address:
39 Fitzroy Street
Grafton Centre
Cambridge
CB1 1ER

name: Faculty of Law Cafe - Cambridge Blue
description: An inexpensive and popular cafe located in the Faculty of Law with a large seating area.

name: Astronomy: Library Room A
description: In the old Cambridge Observatory building dating back to 1823.  This room was the sitting room of the Observatory house.
address:
Institute of Astronomy
Madingley Road
Cambridge
CB3 0HA
restriction: Steps at front of building.  Narrow corridors.

name: Rayleigh Library: Main Study Area
description: An area with large desks for use by all students, ideal for private study. Many of these are situated in natural daylight along one wall of the Library. There are four comfy chairs in this area too.
address:
1st Floor
Bragg Building
Cavendish Laboratory 
19 J J Thomson Avenue 
Cambridge

Nip by at breakfast time and you can enjoy treats like banana bread, pastries and toasted brioche with smoked salmon and cream cheese. Come lunch, there are tasty sandwiches in cute packaging, and all day long you can stop by for a home-made sweet treat or cake.

The Greenwich House Cafe provides an airy and spacious place for your lunch.

There are a range of teas and coffees on offer, jacket potatoes, pastries and various sandwiches, paninis, baguettes and snacks, varying from day to day.  There are options available for all sorts of dietary requirements including gluten-free, dairy-free and vegan - just ask.

Outdoor seating is also available for you to make the most of good weather!
address: Greenwich House, Madingley Road, Cambridge, CB3 0TX

name: 1815 Bar

Named after the founding year of the Cambridge Union, the bar is a part of the historical Cambridge Union located in an over 160 years old Victorian Gothic building right in the heart of Cambridge's city centre. 

Lined with signed photographs of famous guests - from Robert Downey Junior to Buzz Aldrin - and with authentic vintage wooden floors, chandeliers, deep leather chairs, and gardens in town, 1815 is open to the public and provides an array of different things, starting from coffees, sandwiches, and pastries in the morning, through wine, beer, and cocktails.

Large windows provide plenty of natural daylight whilst working at the 10 generously sized study spaces available.  The space is temperature-controlled to provide a comfortable working environment throughout the year. Quiet, thoughtful atmosphere.

Cambridge
CB3 0UB
